DESCRIPTION:This page's content changed since the last check. Visit the pa
 ge directly to review the update.\n\nWhat changed (text excerpt):\nAdded:\
 n  + Where to File\n  + Video/Telephonic Hearings\n  + Court Holidays\n  +
  Attorney Reference Guide\n  + Local Rules\n  + -\n  + Links in the Table 
 of Contents\, when clicked\, will take you to the corresponding rule\n  + 
 The Local Rules were last updated on September 28\, 2021 amending Local Ba
 nkruptcy Rules 9013-1 and 9013-2. This updated version of the Local Rules 
 includes all amendments through September 28\, 2021\, and is the official 
 version of the Local Bankruptcy Rules for the District of Maine.\n  + For 
 Interim Rules implementing the Small Business Reorganization Act of 2019\,
  please see the\n  + Standing Order Regarding SBRA Interim Rules\n  + .\n 
  + Rules Amendments\n  + The process for promulgating an amendment to a ru
 le or form involves several levels of consideration and approval\, the fir
 st of which is consideration and approval by the Local Rules Committee of 
 the Bankruptcy Court. For a graphic representation of the rules amendment 
 process\, please see our\n  + Local Rules Amendments flow chart\n  + . Cur
 rent local rule amendments published for public comment\, if any\, appear 
 below. Proposed amendments are published for comment for 30 days. Comments
  should be sent to\n  + Monica Bigley\n  + \, Clerk of Court (please make 
 clear in the subject line of your email that the email is in regard to a p
 roposed local rule).\n  + Revision History\n  + Commencing with revisions 
 made on or after January 1\, 2017\, all amendments to the local rules (sor
 ted by rule) can be found\n  + here\n  + .\n  + \n[diff truncated]\nhttps:
 //www.meb.uscourts.gov/local-rules
